page.title: 09Well Vale Nature Reserve
page.content: Well Vale is a nature trail which takes you through parkland and past a lake. The woodland area is surrounded with trees such as Larch, sycamore, Beech, Scotts Pine and Elm. Near to the trees wild flowers and shrubs are growing e.g primroses, silverweed, field maple and hawthorn shrubs. There is a definite smell of wild garlic and fungi. Although there is little trace, badgers, hares, moles, rats, fieldmice, pheasants and other birds such as Goldfinch and Treecreeper inhabit this beautiful woodland area. In the lake Waterbeetle and Dragonfly larvae are a few of the insects found, while Moorhen and Coot swim on the lake. Pale green leaves of water Starwort lie on top of the peaceful lake. These are just a few beauties of Well Vale.
